The evidence with the title 'Exxon Mobil posts record 4q profit of $10.7 billion - business - US ... ' says Jan 30, 2006  ... Exxon Mobil Corp. posted record profits for any U.S. company on monday — $ 10.71 billion for the fourth quarter and $ 36.13 billion for the year — as the world's biggest publicly traded oil company benefited from high oil and natural-gas prices and solid demand for refined products. 
